value.value: 滑膜関節形態異常

any structural anomaly of any joint in which the articulating bones or cartilages are connected by an articular capsule which encloses a synovial membrane and a synovial cavity (e.g. temporomandibular joint, knee joint)
肢関節形態異常
any structural anomaly of any joint that is part of a (free) limb
most limb joints are synovial, but a few such as the tibiofibular joints are syndesmoses
自脚関節形態異常
any structural anomaly of any limb joint that is part of an autopod
前肢関節形態異常
any structural anomaly of any limb joint that is part of a forelimb
後肢関節の形態異常
any structural anomaly of any limb joint that is part of a hindlimb
腕橈関節形態異常
any structural anomaly of the hinge joint between the head of the radius and the capitulum of the humerus
環椎後頭関節形態異常
any structural anomaly of either of a pair of condyloid synovial joints between the superior articular facets of the atlas and the condyles of the occipital bone
手関節形態異常
any structural anomaly of any skeletal joint that is part of a hand (manus)
中手指節関節形態異常
any structural anomaly of any of the condylar or ellipsoid synovial joints between the heads of the metacarpal bones and the bases of the proximal phalanges
手の指節間関節の形態異常

any structural anomaly of any hinge-joints of the phalanges of the hand; there are two sets in each finger (except in the thumb): (i) proximal interphalangeal joints (PIP), those between the first (also called proximal) and second (intermediate) phalanges and (ii) distal interphalangeal joints (DIP), those between the second and third (distal) phalanges; a similar group of articulations also function in the toes
手首関節形態異常
any structural anomaly of the joint connecting the forelimb zeugopod skeleton with the carpal skeleton
橈骨手根関節形態異常

any structural anomaly of the major condyloid synovial joint of the wrist which occurs proximally between the distal end of the radius and the articular disc of the distal radioulnar joint, and distally by the proximal carpal row (the scaphoid, lunate and triquetral bones)
肩関節形態異常
any structural anomaly of the joint that is formed by the union of the humerus, the scapula (or shoulder blade), and the clavicle (or collarbone)
肩関節形態異常

any structural anomaly of the main articulation of the shoulder joint; the glenohumeral joint is the multiaxial ball-and-socket synovial joint formed by the articular surfaces of the glenoid cavity of the scapula and the head of the humerus
腰帯関節形態異常
any structural anomaly of any skeletal joint that is part of an appendage girdle region
腰帯関節形態異常
any structural anomaly of any synovial joint that is part of a pelvic girdle region
胸帯関節形態異常
any structural anomaly of any synovial joint that is part of a pectoral girdle region
仙腸関節形態異常

any structural anomaly of the synovial joint that forms between the lateral articulating surfaces of the sacrum and the articulating surfaces of the ilium; it is supported by a number of strong ligaments which increase joint stability and reduce the incidence of dislocations
仙腸関節炎症
inflammation of one or both of the sacroiliac joints; it may be a symptom of other inflammatory arthritic conditions
大腿骨サイズ増加
greater than average size of the long bone of the thigh (femur)
大腿骨重量増加
greater than average weight of the long bone of the thigh (femur)
大腿骨サイズの減少
less than average size of the long bone of the thigh (femur)
大腿骨重量減少
less than average weight of the long bone of the thigh (femur)
大腿骨骨折
a crack or break in the long bone of the thigh (femur)
閉鎖孔形態異常
any structural anomaly of the large opening created by the ischium and pubis bones of the pelvis through which nerves and blood vessels pass
股関節形態異常
any structural anomaly of the multi-axial, ball-and-socket synovial joint between the femur head and the acetabulum of the innominate bone
寛骨臼形態異常

any structural anomaly of the large cup-shaped cavity on the anterolateral aspect of the pelvis that articulates with the femoral head to form the hip joint; it is formed by the three bones of the pelvis (the ischium, ilium and pubis) and is the socket portion of the ball-and-socket hip joint
滑膜窩形態異常
any structural anomaly of the shallow, pyriform articular surface located on the lateral angle of the scapula; it is directed laterally and forward and articulates with the head of the humerus
肩甲骨烏口突起形態異常

any structural anomaly of the hook-shaped bone structure that projects anterolaterally from the superior aspect of the scapular neck and serves as an important anchor for several tendinous and ligamentous structures
肩峰の矮小化
reduced size of the outer end of the spine of the scapula that protects the glenoid cavity, forms the outer angle of the shoulder, and articulates with the clavicle
肩峰形成不全
decrease in the number of normal cells in normal arrangement in the acromion, typically resulting in decreased size
足首関節の形態異常
any structural anomaly of a joint that connects the hindlimb autopod and zeugopod skeletons
脛腓関節形態異常
any structural anomaly of a joint that connects the tibia and the fibula
膝関節形態異常

any structural anomaly of the synovial hinge joint formed between the femur, tibia, and patella; it involves two articulations: the tibiofemoral joint, connecting the proximal tibia to the distal femur, and the patellofemoral joint, connecting the patella to the femur; the knee joint allows flexion and extension of the leg, as well as slight medial rotation in end extension, and lateral rotation when unlocking the knee
寛骨臼窩形態異常
any structural anomaly of the roughened depression in the acetabular floor which extends superiorly from the acetabular notch and hosts the ligamentum teres
寛骨臼ノッチ形態異常

any structural anomaly of the deep notch (depression) located anteroinferiorly along the margin of the acetabulum; it is bridged by the transverse ligament and thus forms the acetabular foramen through which nutrient vessels and nerves enter the hip joint; the ligamentum teres has part of its origin from the acetabular notch
寛骨臼唇形態異常

any structural anomaly of the horse-shaped fibrocartilaginous structure that attaches to the peripheral rim of the acetabulum, contacts the articular surface of the femoral head, and blends inferiorly with the transverse acetabular ligament; it increases the depth of the acetabulum, increasing static stability and contributes to hydrostatic pressurization of the intra-articular space, joint lubrication, and load distribution
寛骨臼横靭帯形態異常

any structural anomaly of the fibrous continuation of the acetabular labrum that is completely collagenous and contains no chondrocytes or cartilage; it consists of strong, flattened fibers which cross the acetabular notch and convert it into the acetabular foramen through which nutrient vessels and nerves enter the hip joint; it prevents inferior displacement of head of femur
弓下窩欠如
missing the irregular depression normally found on the posterior inner surface of the petrous portion of the temporal bone just below its crest and above and lateral to the internal acoustic meatus
肘関節脱臼
dislocation of the distal humerus out of the elbow joint, where the radius, ulna, and humerus meet
恥骨体形態異常

any structural anomaly of the flattened medial portion of the pubic bone entering into the pubic symphysis; superior and inferior rami extend from it; the body forms one-fifth of the acetabulum, contributing by its external surface both to the lunate surface and the acetabular fossa; its internal surface enters into the formation of the wall of the lesser pelvis and gives origin to a portion of the obturator internus
恥骨枝形態異常

any structural anomaly of either of the two bar-like processes (branches or rami) of the pubic bone that extend laterally and posteriorly from the pubic symphysis; the inferior ramus articulates with the ischium; the superior ramus articulates with the ilium and forms the front of the acetabulum
恥骨上行枝形態異常

any structural anomaly of the bar of bone, triangular in section, which extends posterosuperiorly from the body of the pubis to form the superior boundary of the obturator foramen; it contributes about one fifth of the articular surface of the acetabulum
恥骨下行枝形態異常
any structural anomaly of the inferior extension from body of pubic bone that meets with the ramus of the ischium below the obturator foramen to form the ischiopubic ramus
腸骨短縮
reduced length of the broad, flaring portion of the hip bone, which is distinct at birth, but later fuses with the ischium and the pubis
腸骨拡大
increased width of the broad, flaring portion of the hip bone, which is distinct at birth, but later fuses with the ischium and the pubis
腸骨体形態異常

any structural anomaly of the thick lower part (base) of the ilium that forms about the upper two-fifths of the acetabulum; its external surface is partly articular, partly non-articular; the articular segment forms part of the lunate surface of the acetabulum, the non-articular portion contributes to the acetabular fossa; the internal surface of the body is part of the wall of the lesser pelvis and gives origin to some fibers of the obturator internus; below, it is continuous with the pelvic surfaces of the ischium and pubis, only a faint line indicating the place of union
腸骨窩形態異常

any structural anomaly of the large, smooth, concave surface on the internal surface of the ilium; the fossa is bounded above by the iliac crest, below by the arcuate line, and in front and behind, by the anterior and posterior borders of the ilium; it gives origin to the iliacus muscle
腸骨翼形態異常
any structural anomaly of the large, expanded (wing-like) portion of the ilium which bounds the greater pelvis laterally
腸骨稜形態異常

any structural anomaly of the superior border of the wing of ilium and the superolateral margin of the greater pelvis; it runs from the anterior superior iliac spine to the posterior superior iliac spine; many of the important abdominal and core muscles are attached to the iliac crest
